---
import Base from "@/layouts/base.astro";
import ComparisonNav from "@/components/comparison/nav.astro";
import ComparisonHero from "@/components/comparison/hero.astro";
import FeatureTable from "@/components/comparison/feature-table.astro";
import Section from "@/components/comparison/section.astro";
import ComparisonCta from "@/components/comparison/cta.astro";
import Disclaimer from "@/components/comparison/disclaimer.astro";
import Footer from "@/components/footer.astro";

const locale = "en";
---

<Base
  title="CallWise vs Gong — AI Call Scoring for Growth Teams"
  description="Get Gong-level conversation intelligence with built-in VoIP and CRM. No $50K platform fee. CallWise starts at ~$26/user/mo. Try free for 14 days."
  locale={locale}
>
  <ComparisonNav locale={locale} competitorName="Gong" />

  <main>
    <ComparisonHero
      title="Gong-Level Call Intelligence"
      titleGradient="Without the Enterprise Price Tag"
      subtitle="Same AI call scoring. 90% less cost. VoIP and CRM included."
      ctaText="Start Free Trial"
      ctaUrl="https://app.callwise.ai"
      microCopy="14-day free trial · No credit card · No sales call required"
    />

    <Section title="Who Gong Is Built For (And Who It's Not)">
      <p>
        Gong pioneered AI-powered conversation intelligence. For enterprise revenue teams with 100+ reps and $60K+ annual budgets, it's the standard. Gong's Revenue Intelligence platform, deal analytics, and forecasting capabilities are built for Fortune 500 sales organizations.
      </p>
      <p>
        But if you're a <strong>5–20 person sales team</strong>? Gong's pricing model doesn't work. The per-user fees plus platform costs can exceed what your entire tech stack costs today. And you still need a separate dialer and a separate CRM.
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section title="The Cost Breakdown" variant="highlight">
      <p>
        According to third-party estimates, Gong pricing starts at approximately <strong>$100–150/user/month</strong> plus a separate platform fee that can range from <strong>$5,000 to $50,000 annually</strong>. For a 10-person team, that's roughly <strong>$18,000/year or more</strong>.
      </p>
      <p>
        CallWise starts at <strong>~$26/user/month</strong> for Starter, <strong>~$52/user/month</strong> for Professional, and <strong>~$87/user/month</strong> for Business. A 10-person team on Professional costs <strong>~$520/month ($6,240/year)</strong> — with VoIP and CRM included. No platform fee. No separate dialer subscription.
      </p>
      <p>
        <em>Note: Gong pricing is not publicly listed. Figures above are based on third-party estimates and may vary.</em>
      </p>
    </Section>

    <FeatureTable
      title="Feature Comparison"
      competitorLabel="Gong"
      rows={[
        { feature: "AI call scoring", callwise: "✅ 28 metrics", competitor: "✅ Proprietary" },
        { feature: "Explainable AI (SHAP)", callwise: "✅ Why this score", competitor: "❌ Black-box" },
        { feature: "Per-45s micro-coaching windows", callwise: "✅", competitor: "❌" },
        { feature: "Built-in VoIP", callwise: "✅ Native", competitor: "❌ Requires dialer" },
        { feature: "CRM with deal pipeline", callwise: "✅", competitor: "❌ Requires CRM" },
        { feature: "Auto CRM data entry", callwise: "✅", competitor: "❌" },
        { feature: "SMS meeting reminders", callwise: "✅", competitor: "❌" },
        { feature: "Objection detection", callwise: "✅", competitor: "✅" },
        { feature: "Competitive mentions", callwise: "✅", competitor: "✅" },
        { feature: "Revenue forecasting", callwise: "❌", competitor: "✅" },
        { feature: "Self-serve free trial", callwise: "✅ 14 days, no CC", competitor: "❌" },
        { feature: "Public pricing", callwise: "✅", competitor: "❌" },
        { feature: "Languages", callwise: "38+", competitor: "70+" },
        { feature: "Pricing (10 users/mo)", callwise: "~$520", competitor: "~$1,500+" },
      ]}
    />

    <Section title="What You Get with CallWise">
      <p>
        CallWise gives you the core of what makes Gong powerful — AI call scoring, objection detection, competitive intelligence, sentiment analysis, coaching insights — but packages it with the phone system and CRM you also need.
      </p>
      <p><strong>Key capabilities:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>28-metric AI scoring with SHAP explainability</strong> — you see WHY each score was given</li>
        <li><strong>Per-45-second micro-coaching windows</strong> that pinpoint the exact moments in a call</li>
        <li><strong>AI agent with 21 tools</strong> that drafts follow-ups and fills CRM fields automatically</li>
        <li><strong>Built-in VoIP</strong> with call recording</li>
      </ul>
    </Section>

    <Section title="The Architectural Difference">
      <p>
        <strong>Gong is an overlay:</strong> you need a phone system + CRM + Gong = 3 subscriptions, 3 logins, 3 billing cycles.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>CallWise is all-in-one:</strong> VoIP + CRM + AI scoring = 1 subscription, 1 login.
      </p>
      <p>
        For growth-stage teams, this matters. Fewer tools means faster onboarding, less context-switching, and one vendor relationship instead of three.
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section title="What Gong Does Better (We're Being Honest)" variant="honesty">
      <p>
        Gong has a <strong>massive data flywheel</strong> from 5,000+ customers, deeper <strong>revenue forecasting</strong> with their Revenue Intelligence platform, support for <strong>70+ languages</strong> (vs our 38+), <strong>enterprise compliance certifications</strong> (SOC 2, HIPAA) we're still working toward, and sophisticated <strong>deal analytics</strong>.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you're a Fortune 500 company with 100+ reps, Gong is built for you. <strong>CallWise is built for growth-stage teams (5–50 reps)</strong> who need conversation intelligence without enterprise complexity and cost.
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section title="Who Switches from Gong (And Why)">
      <ul>
        <li>Teams that outgrew "we need Gong" but <strong>never grew into Gong's price tier</strong></li>
        <li>Teams that want <strong>VoIP + CRM + AI scoring</strong> without managing 3 separate vendors</li>
        <li>Startups and SMBs where <strong>every dollar of tech spend</strong> needs to deliver measurable coaching impact</li>
      </ul>
    </Section>

    <ComparisonCta
      title="Start Scoring Calls in Minutes"
      subtitle="No $50K platform fee. No sales call required. Just sign up and start."
      ctaText="Start 14-Day Free Trial"
      ctaUrl="https://app.callwise.ai"
      features={["No credit card", "Built-in VoIP", "CRM included", "Self-serve setup"]}
    />

    <Disclaimer competitors={["Gong"]} locale={locale} />
  </main>

  <Footer locale={locale} />
</Base>
